section: bytecode
synopsis: Allocate static constructors for bytecode, fixing segfaults when
          certain programs are loaded by the bytecode interpreter
issues: #25636
mrs: !15221

description: {
    Static data constructor applications are allocated
    directly on the heap by the bytecode linker (using the new
    primop newConApp#), rather than compiled and linked as BCOs.

    Fixes correctness of bytecode-linking unlifted data
    constructors (typically originated from top-level nullary
    data constructors).
}

